114
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:45,060
One thousand five hundred microsieverts an
hour.

115
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:52,060
You know if we stayed here for a couple hours
we’d receive our annual dose of background

116
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:54,430
radiation.

117
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:59,160
That basement was the most radioactive place
I visited and it's one of the most radioactive

118
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,480
places on earth.

119
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:04,769
If I'd stayed down there for one hour I would’ve
received 2000 microsieverts.

120
00:09:04,769 --> 00:09:08,079
That's a years worth of natural background
radiation.

121
00:09:08,079 --> 00:09:10,839
Every yellow pixel here represents a banana.

122
00:09:10,839 --> 00:09:15,120
Now that might seem like a lot, but consider
that in a CT scan the patient receives about

123
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,410
7000 microsieverts.

124
00:09:17,410 --> 00:09:20,769
That's three years worth of natural backround
radiation.

125
